net.i2p.router.transport.udp

Class InboundMessageFragments

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.i2p.router.transport.udp.InboundMessageFragments

  • class InboundMessageFragments
extends Object
    Organize the received data message fragments, feeding completed messages to the MessageReceiver and telling the PeerState to ACK. In addition, it drops failed fragments and keeps a minimal list of the most recently completed messages (even though higher up in the router we have full blown replay detection, its nice to have a basic line of defense here).
